    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "@nicolasnoble that's a fair point, but it's important to note that there are many dependency management systems that don't do a good job of accommodating version pinning (e.g. npm without shrinkwrap, golang).\r\n\r\nWithout having release notes to guide backwards-incompatible updates, we're often blindly updating to the latest version and hoping nothing breaks, and then not knowing why it's broken when it does."
  },
