    "created_at": "2017-04-28T20:47:11Z",
    "updated_at": "2017-04-28T20:47:11Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "So, define backwards-incompatible updates ? We've been really hard at work to make sure we're following semver in every aspect of the release process of gRPC. Meaning that if you upgrade to a 1.x version and something breaks, that would be an actual bug we'd need to hurry to fix.\r\n\r\nI'm kind of trying to say we're trying to do one better: you shouldn't care about reading the release notes if all you're doing is blindly updating to the latest version."
